<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Loader uses a method (LoadFile) to load a file.
If $dirs is an array, the function adds all dirs in $dir to the path and then try to load the file.
include tries to get the file from all the dirs in include_path and log a warning for each dir where the file cannot be found.</p>

<p>Using a file_exists for each dir to find the file, then including the file with his full path would be better.
On a "big" application, a page can load many files and generate a lot of lines into the log file (or into firebug in my case) for nothing.</p>

